[0.001, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[1;3Hthe stations that do not support parsing of the Multiple BSSID element will\u001b[2;3Hnot be able to connect to the non-transmitting interfaces.\u001b[15X\u001b[3;2H\u001b[16X\r\n# Enhanced Multiple BSSID Advertisements (EMA)\r\n# When enabled, the non-transmitting interfaces are split into multiple\u001b[6;3HBeacon frames. The number of Beacon frames required to cover all the\u001b[7;3Hnon-transmitting profiles is called the profile periodicity.\u001b[11X\u001b[8;2H\u001b[68X\r\n# Refer to IEEE Std 802.11-2020 for details regarding the procedure and\r\n# required MAC address assignment.\u001b[11;2H\u001b[70X\u001b[12;3HFollowing configuration is per radio.\u001b[34X\u001b[13;3H0 = Disabled (default)\u001b[52X\u001b[14;3H1 = Multiple BSSID advertisement enabled.\r\n# 2 = Enhanced multiple BSSID advertisement enabled.\r\n#mbssid=0\u001b[17;2H\u001b[19X\u001b[18;3HThe transmitting interface should be added with the 'interface' option while\u001b[19;3Hthe non-transmitting interfaces should be added using the 'bss' option.\u001b[5X\u001b[20;3HSecurity configuration should be added separately per interface, if required.\u001b[21;2H\u001b[78X\u001b[22;3HExample:\u001b[68X\u001b[23;2Hmbssid=2\u001b[70X\u001b[24;2Hinterface=wlan2    \u001b[25;2Hctrl_interface=/run/hostapd\u001b[42X\u001b[26;2Hwpa_passphrase=0123456789\u001b[47X\u001b[27;2Hieee80211w=2\u001b[28;3Hae_pwe=1\u001b[49X\r\n#auth_algs=1\u001b[30;2Hwpa=2\u001b[24X\u001b[31;2Hwpa_pairwise=CCMP\u001b[52X\u001b[32;2Hssid=<SSID-0>\u001b[57X\u001b[33;3Hridge=br-lan    \u001b[34;2Hwpa_key_mgmt=SAE\u001b[8X\u001b[35;3Hssid=00:03:7f:12:84:84\r\n#\nbss=wlan2-1\u001b[24X\u001b[38;2Hctrl_interface=/run/hostapd\u001b[51X\u001b[39;2Hwpa_passphrase=0123456789\u001b[43X\u001b[40;2Hieee80211w=2\u001b[13X\u001b[41;2Hsae_pwe=1\u001b[32X\u001b[42;2Hauth_algs=1\u001b[43;2Hwpa=2\u001b[22X\u001b[44;2Hwpa_pairwise=CCMP\u001b[45;2Hssid=<SSID-1>\u001b[16X\u001b[46;2Hbridge=br-lan\u001b[47;2Hwpa_key_mgmt=SAE\u001b[11X\u001b[48;2Hbssid=00:03:7f:12:84:85\u001b[49;150H\u001b(B\u001b[0;7m3383,1         Bot\u001b[2 q\u001b[?1002h\u001b[?1006h\r\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
